With Doranbau's support,
it's your turn, Blaster Dark!

283
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:28,422
Ahh!

284
00:15:28,422 --> 00:15:31,292
♪

285
00:15:31,292 --> 00:15:33,394
You can't deny it now, Kai.

286
00:15:33,394 --> 00:15:35,496
I've gotten stronger!

287
00:15:35,496 --> 00:15:38,232
All because
I wanted to fight you,

288
00:15:38,232 --> 00:15:40,134
but I want to
hear you say it.

289
00:15:40,134 --> 00:15:41,936
Say that I'm strong!

290
00:15:43,504 --> 00:15:44,939
Marron will guard.

291
00:15:44,939 --> 00:15:48,009
♪

292
00:15:48,009 --> 00:15:50,144
Then Gordon will intercept,

293
00:15:50,144 --> 00:15:51,412
and with his skill,

294
00:15:51,412 --> 00:15:53,481
the shield doubles
in strength.

295
00:15:53,481 --> 00:15:56,083
♪

296
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:57,318
No way.

297
00:15:57,318 --> 00:15:58,219
Ah!

298
00:15:58,219 --> 00:15:59,320
But...

299
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:01,255
it's impossible!

300
00:16:01,255 --> 00:16:02,156
Ha!

301
00:16:02,156 --> 00:16:03,524
Why?

302
00:16:03,524 --> 00:16:05,126
I should have
beaten you this turn,

303
00:16:05,126 --> 00:16:07,495
just like my
Psyqualia said I would!

304
00:16:07,495 --> 00:16:11,332
This isn't the way
I pictured it!

305
00:16:11,332 --> 00:16:15,102
You're still weak because you
rely on that power, Aichi.

306
00:16:15,102 --> 00:16:16,537
You're kidding me.

307
00:16:16,537 --> 00:16:18,739
How can you say that
after I worked so hard

308
00:16:18,739 --> 00:16:20,274
to get good enough
to fight you?

309
00:16:21,042 --> 00:16:22,176
If I'm so weak,

310
00:16:22,176 --> 00:16:24,378
then how come we're
winning at Nationals, huh?

311
00:16:25,179 --> 00:16:27,381
I defeated the Jurassic Army.

312
00:16:27,381 --> 00:16:30,484
It was me that beat
the Brilliant Stars!

313
00:16:30,484 --> 00:16:32,954
Is that your
idea of strength?

314
00:16:32,954 --> 00:16:36,090
Psyqualia gives you an unfair
advantage and nothing more.

315
00:16:37,258 --> 00:16:40,895
Allow me to show you what
real strength looks like.

316
00:16:40,895 --> 00:16:42,463
Final turn.

317
00:16:42,463 --> 00:16:45,866
♪

318
00:16:45,866 --> 00:16:48,936
Knights of the White Light,
please show him the way.

319
00:16:48,936 --> 00:16:50,938
See the king as he once was!

320
00:16:50,938 --> 00:16:54,141
I ride the Vanguard!

321
00:16:54,141 --> 00:16:55,810
Alfred Early!

322
00:16:55,810 --> 00:17:02,149
♪

323
00:17:02,149 --> 00:17:06,120
If you're using that unit,
then you're planning to...

324
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:07,855
With Alfred's skill,

325
00:17:07,855 --> 00:17:11,325
I superior call Blaster
Blade to the rear guard.

326
00:17:11,325 --> 00:17:13,427
♪

327
00:17:13,427 --> 00:17:15,730
Blaster Blade, why?

328
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:20,501
♪

329
00:17:20,501 --> 00:17:21,235
Picture it.

330
00:17:23,571 --> 00:17:27,174
The two of us have
appeared in spirit form

331
00:17:27,174 --> 00:17:30,478
on the surface of
the Planet Cray.

332
00:17:30,478 --> 00:17:32,580
(gasps)

333
00:17:33,814 --> 00:17:36,517
You haven't forgotten,
Aichi Sendou.

334
00:17:36,517 --> 00:17:37,718
Think back.

335
00:17:37,718 --> 00:17:40,121
Remember the time
you almost lost me?

336
00:17:40,121 --> 00:17:42,189
You were strong then.

337
00:17:42,189 --> 00:17:45,326
♪

338
00:17:45,326 --> 00:17:49,263
Your classmate stole
me away from you.

339
00:17:49,263 --> 00:17:51,432
Morikawa, hand it over.

340
00:17:51,432 --> 00:17:53,167
Come on, it means
a lot to me.

341
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:55,036
I won this in a
game of Vanguard,

342
00:17:55,036 --> 00:17:58,272
so there's no way I'm
gonna give it up easily.

343
00:17:58,272 --> 00:18:00,207
Mm, fine then!

344
00:18:00,207 --> 00:18:02,810
I'll fight you
to get it back!

345
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:05,146
Okay, kid, it's a deal.

346
00:18:05,146 --> 00:18:08,416
Challenging Kai to a fight
took a lot of courage.

347
00:18:08,416 --> 00:18:09,784
Don't you get it?

348
00:18:09,784 --> 00:18:12,820
The strength you've been after
was inside you all along.

349
00:18:14,588 --> 00:18:17,158
It was inside me?

350
00:18:17,158 --> 00:18:19,026
Really?

351
00:18:19,026 --> 00:18:19,994
That's right.

352
00:18:22,129 --> 00:18:25,433
You've always been afraid,
hiding from your problems

353
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:27,601
and running away
when things got tough.

354
00:18:27,601 --> 00:18:29,603
That's how you used to be.

355
00:18:29,603 --> 00:18:31,706
♪

356
00:18:31,706 --> 00:18:34,342
But now you're the kind of
guy that faces his problems

357
00:18:34,342 --> 00:18:35,943
without fear in his heart.

358
00:18:35,943 --> 00:18:37,978
You see, your strength
doesn't come from

359
00:18:37,978 --> 00:18:39,513
the deck you're using,

360
00:18:39,513 --> 00:18:43,584
and your Psyqualia isn't
making you stronger either.

361
00:18:43,584 --> 00:18:45,219
Stop it!

362
00:18:45,219 --> 00:18:46,253
You don't know!

363
00:18:46,253 --> 00:18:48,823
I owe everything
to Psyqualia!

364
00:18:48,823 --> 00:18:51,792
Without this power,
I'd be nothing!

365
00:18:51,792 --> 00:18:54,261
You don't believe that.

366
00:18:55,763 --> 00:18:58,833
You were getting
stronger on your own.

367
00:18:58,833 --> 00:18:59,967
Think back.

368
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:01,102
Before you got that power,

369
00:19:01,102 --> 00:19:02,970
the only thing you
wanted was to fight me.

370
00:19:02,970 --> 00:19:06,540
♪

371
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,309
You know it, Aichi.

372
00:19:08,309 --> 00:19:11,645
This isn't what you
pictured for our battle.

373
00:19:11,645 --> 00:19:15,249
It's true, I wanted to be
your equal and friend.

374
00:19:15,249 --> 00:19:23,824
♪

375
00:19:23,824 --> 00:19:24,959
Ahh!

376
00:19:27,027 --> 00:19:29,563
Kai, I've always
hoped that one day

377
00:19:29,563 --> 00:19:32,266
I would get the chance
to face off with you.

378
00:19:32,266 --> 00:19:36,337
♪

379
00:19:36,337 --> 00:19:38,472
(zapping)

380
00:19:40,141 --> 00:19:42,243
(grunts)

381
00:19:43,811 --> 00:19:44,945
No.

382
00:19:44,945 --> 00:19:46,447
It's not right.

383
00:19:48,082 --> 00:19:51,285
♪

384
00:19:51,285 --> 00:19:53,921
(groans)

385
00:19:53,921 --> 00:19:55,856
What's going on?

386
00:19:55,856 --> 00:19:57,091
I'm sorry.

387
00:19:57,091 --> 00:20:01,662
You're really strong,
but you're not my avatar.

388
00:20:01,662 --> 00:20:04,365
♪

389
00:20:04,365 --> 00:20:06,500
Big mistake.

390
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:10,404
♪

391
00:20:10,404 --> 00:20:11,572
No way.

392
00:20:11,572 --> 00:20:13,040
This is right.

393
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:16,710
I know it because my avatar...

394
00:20:16,710 --> 00:20:20,614
♪

395
00:20:20,614 --> 00:20:23,884
...has been waiting
for me all along.

396
00:20:23,884 --> 00:20:27,021
♪

397
00:20:27,021 --> 00:20:29,023
(sighs)

398
00:20:29,023 --> 00:20:34,762
♪

399
00:20:34,762 --> 00:20:35,863
No.

400
00:20:35,863 --> 00:20:37,631
Not like this.

401
00:20:37,631 --> 00:20:40,801
This isn't the way
it was supposed to be.

402
00:20:40,801 --> 00:20:42,102
It's all wrong!

403
00:20:42,102 --> 00:20:53,681
♪

404
00:20:53,681 --> 00:20:54,415
Mm?

405
00:20:55,883 --> 00:20:56,917
Here you go.

406
00:20:58,752 --> 00:21:00,321
Why would you...

407
00:21:00,321 --> 00:21:01,388
Take it.

408
00:21:01,388 --> 00:21:02,790
It's yours, after all.

409
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:09,663
♪

410
00:21:09,663 --> 00:21:11,932
(cries)

411
00:21:11,932 --> 00:21:19,039
♪

412
00:21:19,039 --> 00:21:20,508
(giggles)

413
00:21:20,508 --> 00:21:22,943
Well, guys, it looks
like it all worked out.

414
00:21:22,943 --> 00:21:35,256
♪

415
00:21:35,256 --> 00:21:36,624
I'm sorry to say it, Ren,

416
00:21:36,624 --> 00:21:38,993
but I don't think Aichi
Sendou is coming by today.

417
00:21:40,494 --> 00:21:42,396
Well, that's a real shame.

418
00:21:42,396 --> 00:21:43,597
Too bad.

419
00:21:43,597 --> 00:21:45,165
I thought the kid
had potential.

420
00:21:47,701 --> 00:21:48,836
Thanks.

421
00:21:48,836 --> 00:21:50,671
He doesn't know
what he's missing.

422
00:21:52,473 --> 00:21:55,175
(giggles)

423
00:21:55,175 --> 00:21:56,377
Mm!

424
00:21:56,377 --> 00:21:58,045
I'm glad he stood him up.

425
00:21:58,045 --> 00:21:59,446
Knock it off, Rekka.

426
00:21:59,446 --> 00:22:00,915
Uh‐‐mm.

427
00:22:00,915 --> 00:22:03,651
♪

428
00:22:03,651 --> 00:22:06,787
Ren Suzugamori
and Aichi Sendou...

429
00:22:06,787 --> 00:22:09,757
♪

430
00:22:09,757 --> 00:22:12,192
...two people
blessed with Psyqualia

431
00:22:12,192 --> 00:22:14,528
walking down totally
opposite paths.

432
00:22:14,528 --> 00:22:17,631
♪

433
00:22:17,631 --> 00:22:19,300
This should make
the tournament finals

434
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:21,001
quite interesting.

435
00:22:21,001 --> 00:22:23,170
♪

436
00:22:26,407 --> 00:22:34,682
♪

437
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,102
‐Hey, bro!
‐Yo!

438
00:24:02,102 --> 00:24:03,437
You guys, I‐‐

439
00:24:03,437 --> 00:24:05,706
You'll never guess what
the manager has planned.

440
00:24:05,706 --> 00:24:08,375
Woo‐hoo, it's another
shop tournament!

441
00:24:08,375 --> 00:24:11,278
Yeah, and I think
I might play.

442
00:24:11,278 --> 00:24:13,313
Guys, I owe
everyone an apology

443
00:24:13,313 --> 00:24:15,416
for how I've been
acting lately.

444
00:24:15,416 --> 00:24:16,550
Sorry.

445
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:18,786
Next time, "Golden Glow."

446
00:24:18,786 --> 00:24:20,454
Hold on, something's wrong.

447
00:24:20,454 --> 00:24:22,790
I can't picture the
fights the way I used to.

448
00:24:22,790 --> 00:24:24,458
Ha‐ha, don't sweat it, bro.

449
00:24:24,458 --> 00:24:25,559
Just have fun!

450
00:24:25,559 --> 00:24:27,695
Yeah, really!

